#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Sunsetting legacy config classes"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "After having migrated the whole Quarkus code base and Quarkiverse extensions to @ConfigMapping interfaces in Quarkus 3.19, we announce the sunsetting of legacy config classes."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid ""
"After having migrated the whole Quarkus code base and Quarkiverse extensions to @ConfigMapping interfaces in Quarkus 3.19,\n"
"we announce the sunsetting of legacy config classes."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Some history"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid ""
"In 2022, we introduced in Quarkus a new configuration infrastructure for extensions based on interfaces annotated with `@ConfigMapping`.\n"
"They were a replacement for the legacy config classes that were used in Quarkus extensions,\n"
"which came with several issues and were specific to extensions (you couldn't use them in applications)."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "The new `@ConfigMapping` infrastructure unified extension and application configuration on the same infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid ""
"In Quarkus 3.19k, released late February this year, we moved all the core extensions to this new infrastructure (except for some classes that were kept for compatibility purposes)\n"
"and deprecated the legacy config classes support, together with dropping close to all the existing config classes: we kept a few for compatibility reasons."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "The extension annotation processor was also modified to require a specific option `-AlegacyConfigRoot=true`."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid ""
"The plan has always been to sunset the legacy config classes so that we could remove all the machinery related to it,\n"
"and offer a single unified configuration mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Current state"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "The current state of the public Quarkus ecosystem is the following:"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "All the Core extensions are using the new ``@ConfigMapping``-based infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "All the Quarkiverse extensions have been updated to use the new ``@ConfigMapping``-based infrastructure (except for `quarkus-logging-json` but we have a https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkus-logging-json/pull/345[pull request ready])."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Some other extensions participating to the Ecosystem CI have also been updated such as https://persistence.blazebit.com/[Blaze-Persistence]."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "We know some of you also develop custom extensions so we highly recommend moving your custom extensions to `@ConfigMapping` as soon as possible, if not already done."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "You can find more information about it in https://quarkus.io/guides/writing-extensions#configuration[our documentation] and a ton of examples in the https://github.com/search?q=repo%3Aquarkusio%2Fquarkus%20%40ConfigMapping&type=code[Quarkus Core repository] or the https://github.com/search?q=org%3Aquarkiverse+%40ConfigMapping&type=code[Quarkiverse extensions]."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "If you have any questions while migrating, please ask them in https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/discussions/categories/q-a[GitHub Discussions], we will be happy to help."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Coming in 3.25"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "In 3.25, we will throw an error when the extension annotation processor is used with `-AlegacyConfigRoot=true`."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "**It won't be possible to build an extension containing legacy config classes with Quarkus 3.25 anymore.**"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Coming in 3.26"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid ""
"In 3.26, we will remove all support for legacy config classes, meaning they won't work anymore.\n"
"**If one of the extensions of your application is using any legacy config class, your application won't build.**"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "Note that since 3.19.4, you get a warning if any of the extensions in your application is using legacy config classes."
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "We will also drop all the compatibility classes we kept until then:"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "`GlobalDevServicesConfig`: use `DevServicesConfig` instead"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "`HttpConfiguration`: use `VertxHttpConfig` instead"
msgstr ""

#: _posts/2025-07-03-legacy-config-classes-sunsetting.adoc
msgid "`HttpBuildTimeConfig`: use `VertxHttpBuildTimeConfig` instead"
msgstr ""

